Package jetbrains.mps.extapi.model

Class SModelBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • jetbrains.mps.extapi.model.SModelDescriptorStub
      • jetbrains.mps.extapi.model.SModelBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModelWithDisposeInfo, FastNodeFinder.Factory, SModelInternal, SModel
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EditableSModelBase, RegularModelDescriptor, TrivialModelDescriptor
    public abstract class SModelBase
extends SModelDescriptorStub
implements SModel
    Base implementation of SModel, with actual model data kept separately, ready for e.g. re-load. This implementation tracks load state of the model data (getLoadingState()) and expects subclasses to update this state appropriately. getModelData() provides access to actual node storage. TODO relocate to [smodel]

        Dispose model data, change model's loading state and dispatch state change event. Base implementation does nothing if there's no initialized model data. Generally, subclasses shall override doUnload() to perform actual cleanup of instance fields.
        Specified by:

      • doUnload

        protected void doUnload()
        Perform actual dispose of model data and setLoadingState(ModelLoadingState) changes loading state}. No loading state event is sent (responsibility of unload(). Subclasses shall override to clean instance fields and generally shall delegate to this implementation first to dispose model data.

      • replaceModelAndFireEvent

        protected void replaceModelAndFireEvent​(SModel oldModel,
                                        SModel newModel)
        This method does nothing about model load state, it updates model descriptor of the models passed and dispatches a notification. Seems reasonable to dispatch proper modelUnloaded/modelLoaded events in addition to modelReplaced as there are listeners that expect either, not both. Especially, in case if load level is changed due to replacement (i.e. was FULL, became INTERFACE) FIXME it's synchronized, do we still need that (with RegularModelDescriptor using distinct lock object) XXX there are two uses in subclasses of not-so-nice EditableSModelBase (lazy and custom) that can't get replaced readily with nice and convenient RegularModelDescriptor.replace() call.

      • getNodeEventDispatch

        @NotNull
public final ModelEventDispatch getNodeEventDispatch()
        CLIENTS SHALL NOT USE THIS METHOD. It's public merely to overcome java package boundaries (those of SModelData implementation and this class). FIXME Once deprecated SModel.setModelDescriptor is removed, visibility shall be changed to protected FIXME This is a hack. We shall pass myEventDispatch the moment internal model is initialized. However, it's tricky to find out exact moment with present approach (getSModelInternal() either returns existing or creates new), fireModeStateChanged is feasible option, but misguiding as well. Refactoring required to split access to SModel internal from initialization. To put event dispatch into smodel.SModel doesn't seem to be an option as we need to add listeners without loading whole model.
